Initialization:

1. Installed VirtualBox to run the VM on. 
2. Downloaded Ubuntu ISO image for Ubuntu 26.04 LTS for VM OS.
3. Setup virtual environment by creating a virtual machine. 
      Allocating 16 Gs of RAM, 4 CPUs, and 120 GBs of storage.
      Networked with the host over a bridged adapter.
4. Pointed the VM to the ISO image for boot and enabled UEFI.
5. Booted up VM and installed Ubuntu OS.  Setup user account with root privileges.
6. Powered down the server and removed the ISO path. Booted up the server 
      from the newly installed OS on the VM.
7. Pinged Google.com to test connectivity.  Connectivity established.

Virtual Ubuntu Server running.
